Data Scientist		Panjiva		Cambridge, MA, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><strong>Description<br /><br /></strong>Panjiva is a highly data-driven company. We’ve built a powerful search and analysis platform on top of 300 million global shipping records while crawling and indexing over 100 million web pages.  Our product has attracted worldwide interest; we have over 1 million unique visitors per month, with 4.5 million requests per day.<br /><br />We’re looking for someone that can help us to solve the data challenges that we know we have, as well as help to identify new opportunities to leverage our data. You’ll be working with a variety of teams across the company: engineering, business development, sales, and design to explore exciting and meaningful problems.<br /><br />We’re looking for someone who can leverage a wide array of statistical techniques at scale.  Responsibilities will include helping us develop the next generation of our product, as well as analysis of our internal metrics to assist the company in making a wide variety of data-driven decisions. Our team uses a range of tools including R, Ruby, and SQL to communicate and visualize results.<br />Some of the types of problems you’ll help solve <ul><li>Fuzzy matching and clustering of data, at scale</li> <li>Natural language processing, robust to messy text and multiple languages</li> <li>Matchmaking between companies in international trade</li> <li>Inference of company structures from individual transaction records</li> <li>Shipment trend prediction and modeling</li> <li>Optimization of search weightings</li> <li>Predictive modeling of customer retention</li> </ul>Requirements <ul><li>B.S, M.S, or Ph.D. in a quantitative field, or equivalent experience</li> <li>Deep statistical knowledge and a broad understanding of analytical and machine-learning techniques</li> <li>Track record of providing valuable insights into large, highly multidimensional datasets</li> <li>Experience with a scripting language, such as R, Matlab, or Python with NumPy or SciPy, and the ability to use it to perform complex analyses of large data sets</li> <li>Solid understanding of relational databases, including advanced query techniques</li> <li>Strong ability to communicate and visualize findings</li> </ul>Nice-to-Haves <ul><li>Background in text analysis / information retrieval algorithms (LSA, SVM classification, etc.)</li> <li>Experience building production software</li> <li>Familiarity with Ruby, Postgres, and libsvm</li> <li>Familiarity with large-scale, distributed data processing techniques (Hadoop, Pig, Hive, etc.)</li> <li>Startup experience</li> </ul>Perks and Benefits <ul><li>Weekly tech talks</li> <li>Competitive salaries and stock options</li> <li>Build or buy your dream computer</li> <li>Awesome coffee, tea and juice</li> <li>Kendall Square Office Twenty-five feet from the Red Line T Stop</li> <li>Nineteen days of Paid Time Off (PTO) and 10 paid holidays</li> <li>Health insurance</li> <li>Hacker Continuing Education Wednesdays i.e., craft beer tasting and ping pong</li> <li>Regular off-site retreats where everybody helps to set company direction and strategy</li> </ul>How to apply<br />To apply, email jobs+datascience at panjiva.com with:<br /><ul><li>Your resume (and, if you have it, your blog, GitHub, etc. handles)</li> <li>A description of an exciting project you’ve tackled in the past, with, if possible, an example of code from that project</li> <li>A paper you think is exciting, with an explanation of what makes you excited about it</li> <br /></ul> <br /><br /> <br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Panjiva is the authoritative and most comprehensive information source for the global trade community. The company’s sophisticated technology makes sense of massive amounts of diverse, fragmented data on more than 10 million companies across 190 countries. Panjiva helps those with a stake in global trade in a number of ways –it helps buyers save money by identifying new suppliers, provides new leads for global suppliers and provides intelligence to keep the entire global trade community in-the-know. Panjiva was founded by CEO Josh Green and CTO James Psota. For additional information, visit: https://panjiva.com.</div>